		   "state" : "open",
		   "body" : "Hey all!\r\n\r\nI'm working on internalizing the `Zodiac` Goodie because its dependencies cause a few issues.\r\n\r\nI'm mostly sorted - but some of the tests are failing due to a few differences between the dates that I've used and those used by the dependency.\r\n\r\nI've used [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zodiac) as a source, and I've found some other sites that have agreed with it - but also some that have disagreed.\r\n\r\nIt's not always clear which year the Zodiac is for, and it seems that the dates can shift slightly?\r\n\r\nRegardless, I've looked at the two main alternatives on CPAN: `Zodiac::Tiny` and `DateTime::Event::Zodiac` (the one that is currently used) and they both hardcode their dates - as have I.\r\n\r\nDoes anyone know a better source than Wikipedia for this? Or even, does anyone *know* the correct dates?\r\n\r\nI'd jut like to mention that I don't do astrology.\r\n\r\n@duckduckgo/community-leaders",
