		   "body" : "**What does your Instant Answer do?**\r\n\r\nLets people perform basic Caesar ciphers on text.\r\n\r\n**What problem does your Instant Answer solve (Why is it better than organic links)?**\r\n\r\nAllows quick encoding/decoding of messages without needing to find a site to do it for you.\r\n\r\n**What is the data source for your Instant Answer? (Provide a link if possible)**\r\n\r\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caesar_cipher\r\n\r\n**Why did you choose this data source?**\r\n\r\nIt is a fairly well known cipher, and Wikipedia provides examples (and goes into some detail).\r\n\r\n**Are there any other alternative (better) data sources?**\r\n\r\n[This](http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/electrical-engineering-and-computer-science/6-00sc-introduction-to-computer-science-and-programming-spring-2011/unit-2/lecture-10-hashing-and-classes/MIT6_00SCS11_ps4.pdf) pdf contains a broader overview in a more programatic manner, but is probably less useful for non software-oriented persons.\r\n\r\n**What are some example queries that trigger this Instant Answer?**\r\n\r\n`caesar cipher 2 text`\r\n\r\n`caesar -2 vgzv`\r\n\r\n**Which communities will this Instant Answer be especially useful for? (gamers, book lovers, etc)**\r\n\r\nPeople who are playing around with ciphers and/or want to decrypt small text.\r\n\r\n**Is this Instant Answer connected to a DuckDuckHack [Instant Answer idea](https://duck.co/ideas)?**\r\n\r\nNot to my knowledge.\r\n\r\n**Which existing Instant Answers will this one supercede/overlap with?**\r\n\r\nHopefully none (I haven't come across any issues). Technically the ROT13 cipher is just a Caesar cipher with shift 13, but I doubt that'd cause any issues.\r\n\r\n**Are you having any problems? Do you need our help with anything?**\r\n\r\nI've included two spellings, `caesar` and `ceasar` (`caesar` is correct, but I've seen people spell it `ceasar`), do you think I should include `ceaser` as well?\r\n\r\n**What does the Instant Answer look like? (Provide a screenshot for new or updated Instant Answers)**\r\n\r\n![screenshot from 2015-12-11 19 11 54](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8598426/11753076/300fd104-a03b-11e5-85d1-77421665b000.png)\r\n![screenshot from 2015-12-11 19 12 20](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/8598426/11753089/3c7932e6-a03b-11e5-8f90-a097d3188567.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\nPlease place an 'X' where appropriate.\r\n\r\n```\r\n- [X] Added metadata and attribution information (https://duck.co/duckduckhack/metadata)\r\n- [X] Wrote test file and added to t/ directory (https://duck.co/duckduckhack/goodie_tests)\r\n- [X] Verified that instant answer adheres to design guidelines (https://duck.co/duckduckhack/design_styleguide)\r\n- [X] Verified that instant answer adheres to code styleguide (https://duck.co/duckduckhack/code_styleguide)\r\n- [X] Tested cross-browser compatibility\r\n\r\n    Please let us know which browsers/devices you've tested on:\r\n    - Windows 10\r\n        - [] Google Chrome\r\n        - [] Firefox\r\n        - [] Opera\r\n        - [] IE 11\r\n        - [] Microsoft edge\r\n        \r\n    - Windows 8\r\n        - [] Google Chrome\r\n        - [] Firefox\r\n        - [] Opera\r\n        - [] IE 10\r\n\r\n    - Windows 7\r\n        - [] Google Chrome\r\n        - [] Firefox\r\n        - [] Opera\r\n        - [] IE 8\r\n        - [] IE 9\r\n        - [] IE 10\r\n\r\n    - Windows XP\r\n        - [] IE 7\r\n        - [] IE 8\r\n\r\n    - Linux\r\n        - [] Google Chrome\r\n        - [X] Firefox\r\n        \r\n    - Mac OSX\r\n        - [] Google Chrome\r\n        - [] Firefox\r\n        - [] Opera\r\n        - [] Safari\r\n\r\n    - iOS (iPhone)\r\n        - [X] Safari Mobile\r\n        - [] Google Chrome\r\n        - [] Opera\r\n\r\n    - iOS (iPad)\r\n        - [] Safari Mobile\r\n        - [] Google Chrome\r\n        - [] Opera\r\n\r\n    - Android\r\n        - [X] Firefox\r\n        - [] Native Browser\r\n        - [X] Google Chrome\r\n        - [] Opera\r\n\r\n```\r\n---\r\nhttps://duck.co/ia/view/CaesarCipher",
