		   "comments" : 2,
		   "state" : "open",
		   "body" : "We recently merged a new Factorial Goodie. The current implementation works, but really this functionality should be a part of the existing Calculator Goodie.\r\n\r\nAs well. the current implementation uses a naive method of calculating the Factorial using recursion via `List::Util::reduce`. This should definitely be switched to use `Math::BigInt`'s `bfac()` method.\r\n\r\nThis will enable us to calculate considerably larger values, however we need to wrap this logic in an `alarm` (or similar) so that we don't spend more than 1s calculating extremely large numbers.\r\n\r\nAlternatively we could enforce a reasonable upper limit on the highest input we're willing to accept. Maybe 10,000? or something smaller, like 1000?\r\n\r\nAny Perl experts out there interested in tackling this one?",
