		   "state" : "closed",
		   "body" : "**Note! There's POD Documentation!**\r\nIn the cloned branch, just go to the `zeroclickinfo-goodies` directory, then type `perldoc lib/DDG/GoodieRole/WhatIs.pm` and enjoy!\r\n\r\n## _WhatIs_ it?\r\n\r\nA GoodieRole that aims to abstract matching certain forms of query so developers can focus on writing the functionality.\r\n\r\n### What sort of Goodies might this benefit?\r\n\r\n~~Any Goodies that want to be able to match queries that can be boiled down to \"What is X in Y?\".~~\r\n\r\n~~I may wish to add to this, for queries such as `What is ACTION X?`, `What is X of Y?` etc...~~\r\n\r\n**_Most if not all!_**\r\n\r\nSome Goodies that would directly benefit from this:\r\n - `PigLatin` - Translations to and from 'Pig Latin'.\r\n - `LeetSpeak` - Translations to, ehem, 'Leet Speak'.\r\n - `EmToPx` - Conversions between `px` and `em`.\r\n - `Ascii` - Conversions between binary and ASCII.\r\n - `Lowercase` - Produces a lower-case version of its input.\r\n - `PrimeFactors` - Returns the prime factors of a number.\r\n - Many others!\r\n\r\n### Usage\r\n\r\nImporting is just like with any other GoodieRole:\r\n\r\n``` perl\r\nuse DDG::Goodie;\r\nwith 'DDG::GoodieRole::WhatIs';\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen you use the `wi_translation` routine to instantiate a matcher:\r\n\r\n``` perl\r\nmy $bin_conv = wi_translation(\r\n    groups => ['written'],\r\n    options => {\r\n        to => 'Binary',\r\n        primary => qr/\\d+/,\r\n    },\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs you see, the `wi_translation` routine takes a hash as an argument, there are several attributes that can be specified which are covered in the module.\r\n\r\nAfter having generated `$bin_conv`, you can use it to match simple queries:\r\n\r\n``` perl\r\nmy $result = $bin_conv->match('What is 71 in Binary?');\r\n$result->{primary};\r\n# 71\r\n\r\nmy $result2 = $bin_conv->match('How do I write 42 in Binary?');\r\n$result2->{primary};\r\n# 42\r\n```\r\n\r\nEasy peasy!\r\n\r\n\r\n## To-do\r\n\r\n*There's always a to-do.*\r\n\r\n### Features\r\n\r\n- [x] Support `translation` forms, e.g. `translate X to Y`.\r\n- [x] Support `conversion` forms, e.g., `convert X to Y`.\r\n- [ ] Support `from` forms - e.g., `translate X from Y`.\r\n- [x] Provide a `full_match` option, for cases when the entire query should be a `what is...`.\r\n- [x] Include user named-captures in the result (So you could match directly on value without needing to extract it).\r\n- [ ] Support verb specification - `How do I VERB X in Y`.\r\n\r\n### Ideas\r\n\r\n- [x] Could make it more general by providing access-points through the Role which use presets to generate good defaults for various query-styles.\r\n\r\n## Converting Goodies\r\n\r\nOver on [one of my branches](https://github.com/GuiltyDolphin/zeroclickinfo-goodies/tree/whatis-prac-conv) I've been working on converting some existing Goodies to use WhatIs.\r\n\r\nWhen I am able to convert a Goodie without changing the tests, managing to remove all (or nearly all) regular expressions designed to filter/match the query and replace this with a single WhatIs matcher, I consider it a pretty good success. (The tests have to pass of course!)\r\n\r\nNot sure if I'll PR with this if WhatIs gets merged - mainly just for proof of concept (and to weed out any bugs). Feel free to check it out!",
