		   "body" : "## Changes\r\n\r\nA quick overview of what has been updated/changed.\r\n\r\n### Updates to `DateMath`\r\n\r\n1. Added support for hours, minutes, and seconds.\r\n\r\n This means you can now do queries such as `today + 7 hours`, and get, for example `16 Jan 2016 11:20:55 EST`.\r\n\r\n2. Added support for using `time` as a triggering word.\r\n\r\n Instead of just being able to do `date today`, `date now` etc..., you can use `time` instead of `date`.\r\n\r\n When `time` is used, a 24hr clock is automatically displayed in output, regardless of the type of operation (adding days or hours etc...).\r\n\r\n3. Provide support for specifying the time in input.\r\n\r\n Example: `01 Jan 2012 00:07:00 CET - 7 minutes`, yields `01 Jan 2012 00:00:00 CET`. The time-zone is optional and should hopefully be automatically detected.\r\n\r\n### Changes to the `Dates` role\r\n\r\n1. Added support for a new date format.\r\n\r\n It is essentially the `HTTP` format without the day, and supporting any TZ.\r\n\r\n An example of `HTTP` format might be: `Sun, 01 Jan 2012 00:00:00 UTC`. An example of the new format would be `01 Jan 2012 00:00:00 BST`.\r\n\r\n I think this format is more flexible - as well as being completely unambiguous.\r\n\r\n2. Allow formatting of dates using the above format.\r\n\r\n I noticed that `Dates` only allowed output in terms of the day, month and year - `0 0 %Y`. I've added an optional flag (that does not affect any existing users of the Role) that tells `Dates` to output in terms of the above format `0 0 %Y %T %Z`. This allows full 24hr clock and time-zone (will try the three-letter variant, but fall back on offset) to be displayed.\r\n\r\n3. Additional exports.\r\n\r\n Provide access to the `time_24h` and `time_12h` regular expressions - they are useful.\r\n\r\n### Changes to `t/SunInfo`\r\n\r\n1. Corrected test times.\r\n\r\n In testing, the main-used time-zone is `EST` (due to test location). The `SunInfo` tests were given in `UTC`, and due to my updates to the `Dates` role, the time-zone was being detected as being `EST`, so I've just corrected them to the 5hr difference.\r\n\r\n Please let me know if I've now made the tests incorrect - I did some testing and it seemed fine.\r\n\r\n## To-Do\r\n\r\n- [x] Convert to template.\r\n- [x] Resolve #2056\r\n- [x] Update to use NumberStyler\r\n- [x] Support 24-hour clock notation (`01 Jan 2012 00:00:17 + 3 seconds`).\r\n\r\n---\r\n[IA Page](https://duck.co/ia/view/date_math)",
