		   "closed_at" : null,
		   "number" : 2644,
		   "comments_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/duckduckgo/zeroclickinfo-goodies/issues/2644/comments",
		   "labels_url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/duckduckgo/zeroclickinfo-goodies/issues/2644/labels{/name}",
		   "comments" : 8,
		   "pull_request" : {
		      "patch_url" : "https://github.com/duckduckgo/zeroclickinfo-goodies/pull/2644.patch",
		      "html_url" : "https://github.com/duckduckgo/zeroclickinfo-goodies/pull/2644",
		      "url" : "https://api.github.com/repos/duckduckgo/zeroclickinfo-goodies/pulls/2644",
		      "diff_url" : "https://github.com/duckduckgo/zeroclickinfo-goodies/pull/2644.diff"
		   },
		   "state" : "open",
		   "body" : "**Note! There's POD Documentation!**\r\nIn the cloned branch, just go to the `zeroclickinfo-goodies` directory, then type `perldoc lib/DDG/GoodieRole/WhatIs.pm` and enjoy!\r\n\r\n**Another Note!** This is a continuation of #2001 - but working off a more public branch so collaboration and/or trying it out is easier.\r\n\r\n## _WhatIs_ it?\r\n\r\nA GoodieRole that aims to abstract matching certain forms of query so developers can focus on writing the functionality.\r\n\r\n### What sort of Goodies might this benefit?\r\n\r\n**_Most if not all!_** \r\n\r\nCheck out https://github.com/duckduckgo/zeroclickinfo-goodies/tree/gd/whatis-conversions for examples.\r\n\r\nSome Goodies that would directly benefit from this:\r\n - `PigLatin` - Translations to and from 'Pig Latin'.\r\n - `LeetSpeak` - Translations to, ehem, 'Leet Speak'.\r\n - `EmToPx` - Conversions between `px` and `em`.\r\n - `Ascii` - Conversions between binary and ASCII.\r\n - `Lowercase` - Produces a lower-case version of its input.\r\n - `PrimeFactors` - Returns the prime factors of a number.\r\n - Many others!\r\n\r\n### Usage\r\n\r\nImporting is just like with any other GoodieRole:\r\n\r\n``` perl\r\nuse DDG::Goodie;\r\nwith 'DDG::GoodieRole::WhatIs';\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen you use the `wi_translation` routine to instantiate a matcher:\r\n\r\n``` perl\r\nmy $bin_conv = wi_translation(\r\n    groups => ['written'],\r\n    options => {\r\n        to => 'Binary',\r\n        primary => qr/\\d+/,\r\n    },\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs you see, the `wi_translation` routine takes a hash as an argument, there are several attributes that can be specified which are covered in the module.\r\n\r\nAfter having generated `$bin_conv`, you can use it to match simple queries:\r\n\r\n``` perl\r\nmy $result = $bin_conv->match('What is 71 in Binary?');\r\n$result->{primary};\r\n# 71\r\n\r\nmy $result2 = $bin_conv->match('How do I write 42 in Binary?');\r\n$result2->{primary};\r\n# 42\r\n```\r\n\r\nEasy peasy!\r\n\r\n\r\n## To-do\r\n\r\n*There's always a to-do.*\r\n\r\n### Issues\r\n\r\n- [x] Kindah a biggie... It does slow down the tests as there is no caching - at the moment it adds in the order of 0.2~0.4 seconds (on my machine - which is quite slow anyway) to any Goodie using it, which is probably a bit *too* much over hundreds of Goodies. ***Priority!***\r\n- [x] Improve handling of `translation` groups - currently `what is conversion` is always triggered, but requires the `to` option to be set.\r\n\r\n### Features\r\n\r\n#### Modifiers\r\n\r\n- [x] Support `translation` forms, e.g. `translate X to Y`.\r\n- [x] Support `conversion` forms, e.g., `convert X to Y`.\r\n- [x] Support `from` forms - e.g., `translate X from Y`.\r\n- [x] Support verb specification - `How do I VERB X in Y`.\r\n- [ ] Perhaps split the `property` group up in terms of singular and/or plural. I don't think we can assume that there is always a _plural_ version for the property - but it might still make sense to say \"What is the X of Y?\".\r\n- [ ] Support stand-alone primaries (i.e., where `primary` can be used on its own).\r\n- [ ] I think the `imperative` group should be renamed to `command` - much more _obvious_ what it means then.\r\n- [ ] We could have a `basic math` modifier. This would support very basic 'mathy' expressions such as `X plus Y`, `X - Y` etc... Obviously it would not support a wide range of 'operators', but could be useful for Goodies like `DateMath` (if I see more examples I'll look into this further).\r\n- [ ] Better modifier/entry customization. I think there's a couple of routes for this: \r\n    1. Build more optional-options into the modifiers. This would allow greater customization through just specifying more options.\r\n    2. Build an inheritance system for the modifiers - this would perhaps allow a greater number of 'smaller' modifiers which could each be a variant of an existing modifier. There are already some modifiers that are 'sub-modifiers': for example `spoken translation` and `written translation`. This might also make modifiers easier to create in general as the majority of the implementation would already be defined.\r\n\r\n#### Matcher\r\n\r\n- [x] Provide a `full_match` option, for cases when the entire query should be a `what is...`.\r\n- [x] Include user named-captures in the result (So you could match directly on value without needing to extract it).\r\n- [ ] Have helper regex functions for use with the entry definitions - e.g., for quoting primary it might be `primary => wi_re_quotes` or similar; or alternatively we could maybe expose some of the `Expression` interface? An alternative would be to fully embed these in groups (e.g., `wi_re_quotes` could become the group `quoted`), this would be a bit less powerful (probably) as you'd have to guess _what_ should be quoted.\r\n\r\n#### Misc\r\n\r\n- [ ] Provide integration with other GoodieRoles - this may include things like using the Dates GoodieRole for date parsing, NumberStyle for parsing numbers etc...\r\n\r\n#### POD\r\n\r\n- [ ] Give a more robust definition of 'results' and ensure there is high/full coverage.\r\n    - [ ] Perhaps mention that user matches can be embedded in the results?\r\n\r\n### Ideas\r\n\r\n- [x] Could make it more general by providing access-points through the Role which use presets to generate good defaults for various query-styles.\r\n- [ ] I'm thinking I need to rethink the way modifiers (not expressions) are handled. Currently it does not feel *super* extensible; you have to define each modifier from scratch. I think the main options would be either modifier inheritance or changing the meaning of options/groups such that options control the minutiae of parsing, but the groups can change the way in which options are *interpreted*. Of course I could try a mix of both :wink:",
